		            <div id="node-106" class="node type-page">



  
  
        
      <div class="content clear-block">
      <p class="summary">Beta Cells in Diabetes seeks to advance clinical care based on current knowledge about the pathophysiology of type 2 diabetes.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Find out more about beta cell physiology</h3>
<p><a class="secondary-overview-play" href="/sites/all/themes/betacell/overview/container.swf">Watch</a> a short video on how to target beta cell function early in the course of therapy or browse <a href="/resources">articles</a> selected by our <a href="/about/leadership">editorial board</a> on pathophysiology and interventions.</p>
<h3>Learn what it means to patient care</h3>
<p>Participate in our interactive<a href="/casestudy"> case studies</a> or listen to a <a href="/podcast">podcast</a> of a conversation between a general internist and a beta cell researcher. Also see our <a href="/faqs-primary-care-community">frequently asked questions</a> about beta cell physiology and its clinical implications.</p>
<h3>Stay current on recent literature</h3>
<p>Read and comment on our <a href="/expertblog">blog</a>, featuring experts in primary care and endocrinology, and sign up for <a href="/mailchimp/subscribe">email&nbsp;updates</a> and <a href="/rss-feeds">RSS feeds</a> for ongoing analysis of new research from our panel of experts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
  
  
