          <li class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first"><div id="node-480" class="node type-blog teaser">


  <h3><a href="/expertblog/vitamin-d-and-t2dm" title="Vitamin D and T2DM">Vitamin D and T2DM</a></h3>

      <span class="submitted">Posted February 11, 2011 by <a href="/expertblog/eugene--wright-jr-md">Eugene  Wright, Jr., MD</a></span>
  
  <div class="meta">
      </div>

  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Dr. Neil Binkley recently gave a presentation at the Southern Regional Conference of the ADA in May of 2010 that has made me rethink a lot of my previously held beliefs about vitamin supplementation and type 2 diabetes (T2DM).&nbsp;He reviewed the data on vitamin D and its potential association with diabetes in general and potential mechanisms of action.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
          <div class="links"><ul class="links inline"><li class="node_read_more first"><a href="/expertblog/vitamin-d-and-t2dm" title="Read the rest of Vitamin D and T2DM.">Continue Reading</a></li>
<li class="comment_comments last"><a href="/expertblog/vitamin-d-and-t2dm#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">2 Comments</a></li>
</ul></div>
      </div>

</div>

      <div class="author">
				<a href="/about/author/eugene-wright-jr-md"><img src="/sites/default/files/imagecache/headshot_small/headshots/Wright.png" alt="Eugene  Wright, Jr., MD" title="Eugene  Wright, Jr., MD"  height="79" width="79" /></a>				<div class="author-name">Eugene  Wright, Jr., MD</div>
				<div class="author-position">General Internist</div>
				<div class="author-link"><a href="/about/author/eugene-wright-jr-md">Biography</a></div>
	</div>  </li>
          <li class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even views-row-last"><div id="node-467" class="node type-blog teaser">


  <h3><a href="/expertblog/genetic-studies-type-2-diabetes" title="Genetic Studies Of Type 2 Diabetes">Genetic Studies Of Type 2 Diabetes</a></h3>

      <span class="submitted">Posted January 26, 2011 by <a href="/expertblog/john-l--leahy-md">John L.  Leahy, MD</a></span>
  
  <div class="meta">
        <div class="terms">Tags: <span  class="taxonomy_term_174 first last"><a href="/category/tags/beta-cell-pathophysiology" rel="tag" title="">beta cell pathophysiology</a></span></div>
    </div>

  
  <div class="content">
    <p>The importance of genetics to type 2 diabetes is obvious to any clinician. Dogma for many years has been that we must identify the genetic mutations in type 2 diabetes as soon as possible.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
          <div class="links"><ul class="links inline"><li class="node_read_more first"><a href="/expertblog/genetic-studies-type-2-diabetes" title="Read the rest of Genetic Studies Of Type 2 Diabetes.">Continue Reading</a></li>
<li class="comment_comments last"><a href="/comment/reply/467#comment-form" title="Add a new comment to this page.">0 Comments</a></li>
</ul></div>
      </div>

</div>

